main event: A report of unidentified flying objects observed over Alexandria, Virginia on August 20, 1962.
interesting points: The object was described as a red light appearing bright and diamond-shaped, moving rapidly across the sky., The sighting lasted for 5-10 seconds and ended with the object disappearing without a sound., The observer speculated the light could be natural, caused by the sunset reflecting off clouds., Three different lights were reported, with witnesses observing pulsating movements., Another observer reported a slow-moving white round object that hovered for 15 minutes before accelerating away.
sighted object: red light and silvery metallic object
witness description: U.S. Air Force personnel and local residents
